title: Washington hold on to beat Southern California
text:
Washington hold on to beat Southern California APOctober 10, 2015, 12:01 am TWN SHARE Tweet LOS ANGELES -- Myles Gaskin ran for 134 yards and a fourth-quarter touchdown and the University of Washington shut down No. 17-ranked Southern California's high-powered offense throughout a 17-12 victory in college football on Thursday. 
Receiver Marvin Hall threw a 27-yard touchdown pass to Joshua Perkins on a trick play early in the second half for the Huskies, who beat former coach Steve Sarkisian in a defense-dominated game. Washington beat a ranked team for the first time under second-year coach Chris Petersen. 
Cody Kessler had two interceptions while passing for just 156 yards on a disastrous night for the Trojans, the popular preseason pick to win the Pac-12 Conference. 
Instead, USC couldn't score a touchdown until Ronald Jones II's short run with 12:02 to play. SHARE
